description.narrative: Knowledge and partnerships for nutritionUNICEF PD-Nutrition, in support to regional offices and country offices and its partners, generates, uses and disseminates state of-the-art knowledge and leverages strategic partnerships to achieve improved nutrition outcomes for children, adolescents, and women, leaving no-one behind, which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition (Covid), Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Every Child to Survive and Thrive By 2021, countries apply child-sensitive policies, innovative community-centered approaches and evidence, to implement development and humanitarian interventions at scale, that enable Every Child to Survive and Thrive
